<!-- entry -->
	<h2 class="date-header">January 26, 2008</h2>


<div class="entry" id="entry-44700988">
			<h3 class="entry-header">Latest DLR Hosting Spec</h3>
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<div class="entry-body">
			<p><a title="hosting by John Lam, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/john_lam/2220796647/"><img height="436" alt="hosting" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2185/2220796647_828b7c6af0.jpg" width="500"></a></p>

<p>I'm working on my Lang.net slides this weekend, and I just realized that I forgot to send out a link to our latest <a href="http://compilerlab.members.winisp.net/dlr-spec-hosting.pdf">DLR hosting spec</a>. Written by the incomparable Bill Chiles, this is a remarkably thorough guide to our hosting API.&nbsp; </p>

<p>If you're stepping through our sources, at some point in time you'll run across scary types like ScriptHost and friends. The sources don't help much here, but page 14 of the spec sure does :) Enjoy.</p>

		</div>
		
					<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/LessIsBetter?i=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iunknown.com%2F2008%2F01%2Flatest-dlr-host.html" type="text/javascript"></script>
		
	</div>
	<div class="entry-footer">
					<p class="entry-footer-info">
				<span class="post-footers">Posted at 12:59 PM </span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://www.iunknown.com/2008/01/latest-dlr-host.html">Permalink</a>
			</p>
		
